{
  "answer": "**Chapter 3 of the Yājñavalkya Smṛti in this corpus (slug: unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6) is titled \"On Expiation (prāyaścittādhyāya),\" but it does not contain any discussion of prayascittas (penances) for killing a Brahmin—unintentional or otherwise.**[^1]\n\nThe chapter covers topics such as:\n- Ritual impurity (āśauca) from birth and death, including durations for different castes, relations, and circumstances (verses ~1–34).[^2]\n- Duties in times of distress (āpaddharma).[^3]\n- Duties of hermits (vānaprastha) and ascetics (yati).[^4]\n- Extensive philosophical, yogic, anatomical, and cosmological content on the Self, creation, saṃsāra, guṇas, and liberation (much of verses ~45–334).[^5]\n\nNo verses address sins like brahmahatyā (Brahminicide) or related penances. Searches across the corpus for terms like \"killing Brahmin,\" \"brahmahatya,\" \"slay Brāhmaṇa,\" and \"penance Brahmin\" yielded no relevant matches in this work.[^6] Traditional Smṛti texts often detail such penances elsewhere (e.g., in Manu Smṛti ch. 11 or Viṣṇu Smṛti), but they are absent here.[^7]\n\n[^1]: Full chapter text retrieved via `read_chapter` (unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6, ch. 3, translation); `citation_url`: /works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/.\n[^2]: E.g., [p-40328e](#p-40328e) to [p-879d87](#p-879d87); `citation_url`: /works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/#p-40328e.\n[^3]: E.g., [p-4a0edb](#p-4a0edb) to [p-d4adaa](#p-d4adaa).\n[^4]: E.g., [p-03f060](#p-03f060) to [p-9604d3](#p-9604d3).\n[^5]: E.g., [p-eaf75a](#p-eaf75a) to [p-e2a99a](#p-e2a99a); `citation_url`: /works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/03/translation/.\n[^6]: Multiple `search_corpus` calls (queries: \"killing Brahmin,\" \"brahmahatya,\" \"penance Brahmin,\" etc.); 0 hits in this work.\n[^7]: The corpus has 37 works; this topic appears elsewhere (e.g., Viṣṇu Smṛti ch. 10 mentions worlds for \"those who kill Brāhmaṇas\"), but not here. `citation_url` for example: /works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/10/translation/#p-24d4f5.",
